  "title": "Maintenance Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Maintenance Engineer (Semiconductor)</strong></u><br />(Outsource Contractor for MNC Company)</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong><br />Maintenance of equipment</p><ul><li>Perform preventive maintenance</li><li>Able to perform and maintain high availability of production machinery and related equipment through effective predictive, preventive and productive maintenance programs</li><li>Perform calibrations on area equipment</li><li>Provide feedback and data to engineer as needed</li><li>Follow safety procedures and area work rules including proper PPE</li><li>Ensure system are well maintained</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Degree in Engineering</li><li>Good learning attitude, independent on-site duty</li><li>Training will be provided for individuals without prior experience</li><li>Full-Time position(s) available</li><li>Knowledge in Wafer Fab Facility preferred</li><li>Candidates are required to handle heavy equipment min 10kgs each</li></ul><p>Location - Woodlands</p><ul><li>Cleanroom Environment</li><li>OT allowance will be given if required to work</li><li>Shift work</li></ul>",
